Cloud VPNs

Type: array of object

All items must be unique

Each item of this array must be:

root Cloud VPN
Type: object

Google Cloud Virtual Private Network (VPN) lets you connect your existing network to your GCP network via an IPsec connection. Alternatively, you can use it to connect two different Google Cloud VPN gateways.

If the conditions in the "If" tab are respected, then the conditions in the "Then" tab should be respected. Otherwise, the conditions in the "Else" tab should be respected.

  • Then

root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN
Type: object
No Additional Properties

root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN vpn_type
Type: const
Specific value: "HA"

root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN label
Type: string

This field will be used to combine with [environment] and [prefix] to generate a unique VPC name

Must match regular expression: ^[a-z][a-z0-9-_]{0,62}$
Examples:

"pci"

"hr"

"finance"

"b2b"

root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN environment
Type: string

If specified this 'Environment' value will override the default value specified in the Terraform module

Must match regular expression: ^[a-z][a-z0-9-_]{0,62}$
Examples:

"dev"

"test"

"stage"

"prod"

root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN prefix
Type: string

If specified this 'Prefix' value will override the default value specified in the Terraform module

Must match regular expression: ^[a-z][a-z0-9-_]{0,62}$
Examples:

"foo"

"bar"

root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN project_id
Type: string

If specified this 'Project ID' value will override the default value specified in the Terraform module

Must match regular expression: ^[a-z][a-z0-9-]{4,28}[a-z0-9]$
Examples:

"phrasal-bank-387121"

"gold-setup-387121"

root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN network
Type: string

The name of the vpc network to be connected with using Cloud VPN.

Must match regular expression: ^[a-z][a-z0-9-]{0,61}(?<!-)$
Example:

"prod-network"

root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN hub_router Hub Router (Manged /w Terraform) bgp asn

Hub BGP Autonomous System Number (ASN). Must be an RFC6996 private ASN, either 16-bit or 32-bit. The value will be fixed for this router resource. All VPN tunnels that link to this router will have the same hub ASN.

  • 16-bit Autonomous System Numbers
  • 32-bit Autonomous System Numbers
root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN hub_router Hub Router (Manged /w Terraform) bgp asn oneOf 16-bit Autonomous System Numbers
Type: number

Value must be greater or equal to 64512 and lesser or equal to 65534

root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN hub_router Hub Router (Manged /w Terraform) bgp asn oneOf 32-bit Autonomous System Numbers
Type: number

Value must be greater or equal to 4200000000 and lesser or equal to 4294967294

root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN hub_router Hub Router (Manged /w Terraform) bgp hub_subnet_advertisements

  • Advertise all subnets visible to the Cloud Router
  • Advertise all subnets visible to the Cloud Router & all Custom subnets specified
  • Advertise all Custom subnets specified
root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN hub_router Hub Router (Manged /w Terraform) bgp hub_subnet_advertisements oneOf Advertise all subnets visible to the Cloud Router
Type: const
Specific value: "DEFAULT"
root Cloud VPN High Availability VPN hub_router Hub Router (Manged /w Terraform) bgp hub_subnet_advertisements oneOf Advertise all subnets visible to the Cloud Router & all Custom subnets specified
